<div>
<h3 class="bac">Summary</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Location: London</li>
	<li>On track for a minimum of a 2:1 degree classification (or equivalent) from any degree discipline</li>
	<li>Fluency in English</li>
	<li>Rotational programme</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">A strategic partner to our business and corporate groups, HR provides the expertise essential for maximizing employees&#39; professional achievement. Working together, the HR Generalist team supported by their specialist partners including recruitment, diversity, learning and development, compensation and benefits and employee relations, provide a comprehensive service to the business.</p>
<p class="bac">At Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Merrill Lynch, people are our most valuable and important commodity. HR is responsible for ensuring that we attract, develop and retain a world class workforce. HR is integral in ensuring a fair and meritocratic working environment and maintaining a positive team culture that celebrates diversity.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information">Overview</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">As an Analyst within HR, you will:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Complete 4 rotations over 2 years, usually including generalist and specialist partner teams</li>
	<li>Collaborate on projects that contribute to business success by building relationships, knowledge and experience that will open doors to a wide range of future career options and opportunities</li>
	<li>Work with your team to create a competitive advantage, and promote an internal and external reputation for excellence</li>
	<li>Learn how HR can support the business in achieving their goals and provide strategic vision to maximise efficiency and success</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information">Training</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>You will take on real responsibility in an assigned role, working with and learning from teams of professionals, including senior experts in their area as well as colleagues from around the globe</li>
	<li>On the job training will form a large part of your continued development once you join your team</li>
	<li>Various events will take place throughout the programme to continue the opportunity for learning and networking</li>
	<li>Through working with a Manager, completing assigned projects and tasks, attending meetings, attending conference calls and presentations and completing research, Graduates will have the opportunity to learn how HR supports the business through engagement with our specialist partners</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

